<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/2004a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d186fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, on the same
                                date, to the Ambassador in France (No. 5382).</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-21T15:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>883. Department’s July 11, 4 p.m., and instruction No. 6017 of July
                                15.<note n="2" xml:id="d186fn2">Not printed.</note> The American
                            Government hopes that His Britannic Majesty’s Government will be
                            disposed to cooperate in the proposed international consortium, more
                            especially since the British Government has repeatedly urged the
                            formation of an American group to participate in loans to China.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>